byline.original: By RAYMOND DANIELL Special Cable to THE NEW YORK TIMES

abstract: Brit and Ital reaction; Mussolini's barter offers and delays on airplane engines for Brit and France cited
snippet: LONDON, March 1--How Premier Mussolini will react when the British begin interfering with Italy's sea-borne coal imports from Germany after today provides one of the most interesting diplomatic riddles of the week....

headline.main: BRITISH SEE ITALY WON BY COAL BAN; Mussolini Is Expected to Make Emphatic Protests but Give In Finally to Trade Deal ROME CHARGES BLACKMAIL Newspaper Says Most Fuel Can Be Brought by Rail-- London Is Skeptical

lead_paragraph: LONDON, March 1--How Premier Mussolini will react when the British begin interfering with Italy's sea-borne coal imports from Germany after today provides one of the most interesting diplomatic riddles of the week.
